      <h2 class="h2">What is it?</h2>
      <p>This is a lightweight accessibility (a11y) scanner that loads a target page in headless Chromium (via Puppeteer) and runs <code>@axe-core/puppeteer</code> to detect common issues. Results are rendered in a readable report with links to remediation guidance.</p>

      <h2 class="h2">How it works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>You submit a URL on the Test page.</li>
        <li>The server launches a headless browser and navigates to the URL.</li>
        <li>axe‑core analyzes the DOM and returns findings (violations, incomplete, passes, inapplicable).</li>
        <li>We summarize the output and provide details for each rule and affected node.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="h2">Technology</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Node.js + Express + EJS</li>
        <li>Puppeteer + <code>@axe-core/puppeteer</code></li>
        <li>Optional telemetry via Azure Application Insights</li>
        <li>Hardened with Helmet and rate limiting on the scanning endpoint</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="h2">Notes & limitations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Some accessibility checks require manual review; see “Incomplete” items.</li>
        <li>Pages requiring authentication aren’t supported unless the environment injects valid session/auth headers.</li>
        <li>Heavy pages may take longer or time out—consider queueing for large‑scale scans.</li>
      </ul>

